50 ms base is aggressive because Redis ought to respond in microseconds â€” a 50, 100, 200 ms spread catches transient pool-exhaustion blips without stretching the request budget.

```ts
import { Observable, timer, throwError } from "rxjs";
import { retry } from "rxjs/operators";

interface Payload {
  id: string;
}

declare const source$: Observable<Payload>;

export function retryUntilAborted$(signal: AbortSignal): Observable<Payload> {
  return source$.pipe(
    retry({
      count: 5,
      delay: (err: unknown, attempt: number): Observable<number> => {
        if (signal.aborted) {
          return throwError(() => err) as unknown as Observable<number>;
        }
        return timer(2 ** attempt * 300);
      },
    })
  );
}
```

The `delay` callback checks `signal.aborted` on each error â€” if the caller has cancelled, the retry budget short-circuits and the original error propagates.

`retryWhen` exposed the whole error stream as an observable you had to transform â€” awkward to type, easy to write an accidental infinite-retry-loop, and the "attempt count" had to be threaded manually via `scan`. `retry({ count, delay })` replaces the common cases with a declarative config: `count` caps attempts and `delay` receives the error and the attempt index.

```ts
import { Observable, timer } from "rxjs";
import { retry } from "rxjs/operators";

interface Reply {
  id: string;
  body: string;
}

declare function callService$(): Observable<Reply>;

export const retried$: Observable<Reply> = callService$().pipe(
  retry({
    count: 3,
    delay: (_err: unknown, attempt: number): Observable<number> =>
      timer(2 ** attempt * 200),
  })
);
```

Cleaner, safer, fully typed â€” and `count` is explicit so the retry budget is obvious at the call site.

```ts
import { MonoTypeOperatorFunction, Observable, timer, throwError } from "rxjs";
import { retry } from "rxjs/operators";

type GrpcCode =
  | "OK"
  | "CANCELLED"
  | "UNAUTHENTICATED"
  | "UNAVAILABLE"
  | "DEADLINE_EXCEEDED";

interface GrpcError extends Error {
  code: GrpcCode;
}

function isGrpcError(err: unknown): err is GrpcError {
  return err instanceof Error && typeof (err as GrpcError).code === "string";
}

export function grpcRetry<T>(): MonoTypeOperatorFunction<T> {
  return (src$: Observable<T>): Observable<T> =>
    src$.pipe(
      retry({
        count: 4,
        delay: (err: unknown, attempt: number): Observable<number> => {
          if (isGrpcError(err) && err.code === "UNAUTHENTICATED") {
            return throwError(() => err) as unknown as Observable<number>;
          }
          return timer(2 ** attempt * 100);
        },
      })
    );
}
```

Auth errors don't get better with time â€” short-circuiting on `UNAUTHENTICATED` surfaces the real issue to the caller immediately instead of wasting 4 attempts.
